# Production Release Governance

When the user asks to ship to production (e.g. «можно в прод», «deploy to prod», «выложи в прод»), run the **full release pipeline** in this chat — do not stop after local commits only.

## Required Release Flow (complete every step)

1. **Verify** — run relevant tests and `npm run build`; fix failures before shipping.
2. **Version** — bump `package.json` `version` (patch unless user asked for minor/major).
3. **Commit feature/fix** — one or more commits with clear messages (feature first, then release wrapper if needed).
4. **Release notes** — add entry at top of `components/dashboard/ReleaseNotesPanel.tsx`:
   - date, short title with version,
   - what changed,
   - commit hash (use short hash after commit).
5. **Commit release notes** — separate `docs(release): …` commit if not in the same commit.
6. **Push** — `git push origin main` (or the branch the user specified). Retry with `required_permissions: ["all"]`. If push fails on HTTPS, try `gh` or SSH; report clearly only if auth is missing on the machine.
7. **Deploy** — `npx vercel deploy --prod --yes` from repo root (`required_permissions: ["all"]`). Wait until alias (e.g. applitaxi.space) is ready.
8. **Report** — production URL, Vercel inspect link, version, commit hash(es), and whether `git push` succeeded.

## Guardrails

- Deploy to production **only** when the user explicitly requests it in this chat.
- Do not deploy proactively after implementing a feature.
- Do not skip release notes or version bump for production releases.
- Do not use `git commit --amend` unless user rules allow it.
- Never update git config (user name/email, credential helpers).
- If there are no code changes to ship, confirm with the user before deploying.

## SQL / schema

- If the release adds or changes Supabase schema, remind the user to run the SQL file in Supabase SQL Editor (or `npm run db:apply:*` when applicable) — deploy alone does not apply DB migrations.
